  <Subject Subject_ID="300053279">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300199637</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>planographic printing processes [300199637], printing processes [300199635], printing and printing processes and techniques [300185289], image-making processes and techniques [300053159], processes and techniques by specific type [300053003], Processes and Techniques (hierarchy name) [300053001], Activities Facet [300264090]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Printing method in which the image is transferred from a roller, plate, block, or stone to an intermediary, such as a rubber blanket or roller, then onto the paper or other final surface. It is a method used for printing a large number of impressions. If the original image is created by lithographic technique specifically, use "offset lithography." </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050615/IFLA Glossary for Art Librarians (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Método de impresión en el cual la imagen es transferida de una placa, bloque o piedra a un intermediario, tal como una cinta de caucho, y después a la superficie final. Si la imagen original es creada específicamente por técnica litográfica, úsase "litografía offset”.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Drukmethode waarbij de afbeelding van een plaat, blok of steen wordt overgezet op een andere laag, bijvoorbeeld van rubber, en dan op het uiteindelijke oppervlak. Gebruik 'offsetlithografie' als de originele afbeelding is gemaakt volgens de steendruktechniek.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052458/Elseviers Dictionary printing (1983)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種印刷方式，圖像是從滾筒、印版、刻版或石版，轉移到如橡膠布或滾筒的媒介物上，然後再印製到紙張或其他最後的平面。此技術可用於大量印刷。若原稿圖像是以平版印刷技術產生的，則用「平版印刷術」(offset lithography)一詞。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
